                <h3 class="mt-3 h3">A little bit more about me</h3>
                <h4 class="mt-3 h4">Pre 2017</h4>
                <p>
                    I grew up in a small farming village in the Staffordshire Moorlands Peak District, with my parents
                    and two brothers.
                    My youngest brother has down-syndrome. During this time, I spend a lot of time outdoors. Walking
                    and camping. In school, I developed a passion for
                    art and technology. Taking both at GCSE and A level. I developed a working knowledge of building and
                    repairing my desktop pcs and laptops.
                    Through my research, helping my dad and through study. In 2017 I build my first PC. To
                    create the desired build,
                    I started by researching the different components and peripherals which were the best for my budget.
                    I then used youtube to help direct me
                    on how to install the hardware. To install the software, I used my knowledge. I ran into a few
                    issues when building such as the PSU not functioning as intended.
                    which was due to a faulty power cable. I also ran into a problem with the GPU but managed to fix it
                    by updating the driver. Since then, I have gone
                    on to install additional RAM and install an SSD for better boot time and performance. I run regular
                    os and Diver updates. I also enjoy gaming which led me recently refurbish an old
                    Gameboy Advance. replacing the shell, buttons and screen. My A-level's was the first time I
                    encountered coding. Learning the basics of HTML and CSS. I also studied units on
                    business data management using Microsoft EXCEL.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 mt-3 shadow" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="center-bottom">
                <h4 class="mt-3 h4">2017-2020</h4>
                <p>
                    In 2017, I went to university, initially, I studied Graphic Design at the University of Derby. However, I
                    transferred to Wrexham at the start of 2018. To be close to my partner and support her as she became
                    homeless.
                    This time was probably one of the hardest parts of my life so far. But we both wouldn't be where we are
                    today if it hadn't happened.
                    We spent a lot of time in my then-student accommodation. She lived in a homeless hostel in Wrexham. In
                    2019 we moved into our flat thanks to Clywd Alyn housing association.
                    For my degree dissertation, I decided to explore the relationship that art has with technology and
                    whether putting art in different formats added or took away from its experience.
                    I created a mock virtual gallery using Blender. I received the mark of 1st for my dissertation.
                </p>
